http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/KCR%E2%80%99s-gift-to-ex-servicemen/article13985597.ece

The ex-servicemen in the State would get property tax exemption if they have their properties in the name of their wives, said Chief Minister K. Chandrasekhar Rao. As a tribute for their service to the nation, the government has also decided to allocate two per cent of two-bed room houses across the State to the ex-servicemen. The Chief Minister also announced that he would take up responsibility of developing a beautiful Journalist Colony in Warangal which would be a model in the State. He said he would personally supervise the work of construction of colony and soon the Deputy Chief Minister Kadiam Srihari will hold a meeting with the journalists irrespective of their affiliation or union.